    public interface IObsoleteable
    Purpose: Allows marking records as obsolete rather than deleting them. This is typically necessary for reference tables that are referenced by many other tables. The record in the reference table, however, does not know what records point to it.

    When a table implements this interface, the record is marked obsolete rather than deleted.

    Note: the system will not check whether the entity is used, because the system does not know which entities refer to a record in a reference table. For example, if the user marks line as obsolete, the line record will be still in the system and all entities point to it will still show the line.

    The following further functions are planned: Obsolete entities are displayed on the forms that directly manage the reference entity. The screen has a display option to display all or only the ?not-obsolete? entities. On the line management list view obsolete lines will show up with a flag obsolete flag set. Obsolete entities are not shown on any LOV for business entities that related to the reference entity. For example, on the container modify screen the LOV for owner does not show deprecated entities. The user still has the capability to search for obsolete entities. For example, the LOV for owner on the container filter will still show the obsolete entities (for example marked obsolete by crossing the text out).

    Author:
    Andreas Neyer

    Date: Aug 9, 2004
